Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

(5 comments)

Please look at doing this with sessions rather than passing around the token itself all the time. 

You should also not assume that you can reuse the auth_token credentials. These are private to auth_token middleware. If you use the session loading utils in keystoneclient then you can make these credentials the same in conf.

This should be really easy with plugins. get the user id from a login, create trust, scope a new plugin with it and then just use that plugin for the rest of the process.
